.\" Manpage for Simple Shell.
.TH "Simple Shell" 1 "26 November 2021" "1.0" "Simple Shell man page"

.SH NAME
hsh - Simple Shell

.SH SYNOPSIS
hsh (does not support arguments)

.SH DESCRIPTION
Welcome to the Simple Shell project! This program is a simple shell that can be compiled and launched from the command line within any number of Linux versions.

.SH OVERVIEW
The Simple Shell project is a major team project conducted by Martín Vidan and César Calero, students at Holberton School.

.SH RETURN VALUE
The shell returns the error code given by the last completed command followed by either ctrl-d or exit with no status code.

.SH SYNTAX

.SS INTERACTIVE MODE

$ <command> <flags or options>

.SS
EXAMPLE 1:
$ ./hsh
($) /bin/ls
hsh main.c shell.c
($)
($) exit
$

.SS NON-INTERACTIVE MODE

$ <command> <flags or options> | ./hsh

.SS
EXAMPLE 1:

$ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
hsh main.c shell.c file_n.c ...
$

.SH SUPORTTED COMMANDS
.SS ls
- used to list files or directories 

.SS pwd 
- stands for print working directory

.SS ctrl d
- alternative exit from shell 

.SS exit
- exit from shell

.SH BUGS
No known bugs

